Sentencas: The electrochemical behavior of the La0.8Sr0.2MnO3-delta/Zr0.92Y0.08O2 (LSM/YSZ) porous composite anodes in solid oxide electrolysis cell is investigated by impedance spectroscopy over an oxygen partial pressure (pO(2)) range from 0 to 0.6 x 10(5) Pa.
Titulo: Effect of oxygen partial pressure on the electrochemical impedance of La0.8Sr0.2MnO3-δ/Zr0.92Y0.08O2 porous composite anodes in solid oxide electrolysis cell

Sentencas: The differential analysis of impedance spectra (DIS) shows three separate arcs which correspond to three different electrode processes at high, intermediate and low frequencies, respectively.
Titulo: Effect of oxygen partial pressure on the electrochemical impedance of La0.8Sr0.2MnO3-δ/Zr0.92Y0.08O2 porous composite anodes in solid oxide electrolysis cell

Sentencas: Three different electrode processes can be attributed to the migration of oxygen ions from the electrolyte to the triple-phase boundary, concentration impedance associated with dissociative desorption of O2- along the LSM surface and diffusion of oxygen, respectively.
Titulo: Effect of oxygen partial pressure on the electrochemical impedance of La0.8Sr0.2MnO3-δ/Zr0.92Y0.08O2 porous composite anodes in solid oxide electrolysis cell

Sentencas: Interestingly, under low pO(2) (approximate to 0 Pa), the impedance arcs become clearly separated at different frequencies, especially for the anodes with higher porosity.
Titulo: Effect of oxygen partial pressure on the electrochemical impedance of La0.8Sr0.2MnO3-δ/Zr0.92Y0.08O2 porous composite anodes in solid oxide electrolysis cell

Sentencas: Meanwhile, the results demonstrate that the electrode process associated with the low-frequency arc is strongly affected by pO(2).
Titulo: Effect of oxygen partial pressure on the electrochemical impedance of La0.8Sr0.2MnO3-δ/Zr0.92Y0.08O2 porous composite anodes in solid oxide electrolysis cell

Sentencas: Furthermore, the porosity plays an important role in dissociative adsorption and diffusion of oxygen.
Titulo: Effect of oxygen partial pressure on the electrochemical impedance of La0.8Sr0.2MnO3-δ/Zr0.92Y0.08O2 porous composite anodes in solid oxide electrolysis cell
